It is our great pleasure to announce Nickel Creek’s fifth studio album, “Celebrants,” an 18 track exploration of togetherness to be released in totality on March 24th! Today, you can listen to the first single, “Strangers,” and pre-order the album [link in bio]. 

If you happened to log into one of the live streams we did early in 2021, you saw us at the very beginning of the process. There were many trips across the country to write and make demos, a constantly evolving shared-note of lyrics, and life-affirming collaboration with heroes @mikeelizondojr on bass and Eric Valentine (@nerdentine) in the producer’s (and engineer’s) chair, culminating in four weeks at RCA Studio A in Nashville. As much fun as we’ve had making music together over the years, this project broke the joy meter. We’re very proud of the results, and can’t WAIT to share them with you.
ICYMI! We have a new album, ‘Celebrants,’ out March 24. The first single, “Strangers,” is streaming everywhere now! Listen + watch the full performance video at the link in bio.

HOT OFF THE PRESSES!!! We are psyched beyond description to share the second single from Celebrants, “Holding Pattern.” This one contains themes (both lyrical and musical) that we develop over the course of the LP. The circular contrapuntal guitar figures brought the holding pattern imagery to mind. Here’s to true love keeping us airborne when it isn’t safe to land! Listen now at the link in bio.
I will never tire of this delightful display of counterpoint(?) from Sean and Chris. And in honor of their birthday weekend, I share it with you.  Happy Birthdays Sean and Chris! - Sara

HOORAAAAYYYYY!!!!!! After months and months of collaborative dreaming/sketching/writing/frustration/revision/hope/shedding/terror/determination/joy, fueled by exceedingly light roasted coffee and Home on the Ranges (2oz rye, .5 Cointreau, .5 Carpano Antica, two dashes Angostura, stirred, big rock, lemon and orange peels), our fifth LP, “Celebrants,” is out of the nest and would love to take up permanent residence in your ears!

The thing that’s being celebrated throughout the course of the record’s 18 interconnected tracks is Togetherness, in all its soul-restoring, heartbreaking, mind-numbing, change-inciting glory, so we highly recommend inviting a couple friends over, maybe making a round of the cocktail above, pressing play, and then talking it all over, whatever “it” may be.

We look greatly forward to hearing what you think whenever we see you next, whether it be out by the bus after a show, in an airport, or at a coffee shop, so don’t be a stranger, and thank you so so SO much for continuing to make our band a part of your lives. WE LOVE YOU. Happy listening!!!

Last night’s @nickelcreek show in NYC was the final of three shows with the one and only @mikeelizondojr on the ol’ doghouse. He’s the genius who played all bass parts on Celebrants but we have all had the good fortune of getting to work with Mike a lot over the almost 20 years we’ve know him and we’re just so grateful for any time we get to make music or even just hang with him. He’s an absolute legend and hero and we’re so grateful he was able to step in for our beloved bass player @jeffpicker who is ALSO one of the absolute baddest asses out there. Check him out with @eastnashgrass when he’s not with us this year. So great! Anyway folks, it’s an embarrassment of bass riches but rest assured we fully realize it. Jeff will be back with us when we reconvene July 6th in Seattle to begin the third leg of Celebrants touring. 📸 by @clairecoffee

That’s a wrap on the September leg of our tour!  Incredible.  Thanks to each of you who came out to the shows in the UK, Europe and the States! 

And HUGE thanks to Jeff Picker who crushes the bass every night on stage (even with food poisoning) and our crew Justin Tamplin, Tim Springette, Jarod Harmon, Tim Reitnouer, Chris Hill, Jody March and TM Katie Muldoon. Y’all make it all possible by taking the early flights (so much carnet) dealing with impossibly tiny transport and somehow never complaining. You are our heroes and we quite literally couldn’t have done it without you.

Lets pick it back up in October, shall we?! We are heading west!

XOXO
